# Multi-Modal Vision Model Support

KaiROS.AI already uses LLamaSharp v0.26.0 which introduced the `LLavaWeights` class and multi-modal `InteractiveExecutor` overloads. This plan adds end-to-end vision support: catalog vision models, load a companion mm-proj file alongside the main GGUF, let users attach images in chat, and stream a vision-aware response.

## Proposed Changes

---

### 1. Models

#### [MODIFY] [LLMModelInfo.cs](file:///c:/Users/User/source/repos/avikeid2007/Kairos.local/KaiROS.AI/Models/LLMModelInfo.cs)
- Add `bool IsVisionModel` — marks models that support image input.
- Add `string? MmProjDownloadUrl` — URL for the companion mm-proj GGUF.
- Add `string? MmProjLocalPath` — resolved local path once downloaded.

#### [MODIFY] [ChatMessage.cs](file:///c:/Users/User/source/repos/avikeid2007/Kairos.local/KaiROS.AI/Models/ChatMessage.cs)
- Add `string? AttachedImagePath` — stores the path of an attached image on user messages.

---

### 2. Model Catalog ([appsettings.json](file:///c:/Users/User/source/repos/avikeid2007/Kairos.local/KaiROS.AI/appsettings.json))

#### [MODIFY] [appsettings.json](file:///c:/Users/User/source/repos/avikeid2007/Kairos.local/KaiROS.AI/appsettings.json)
Add vision-capable models:
- **LLaVA 1.6 Mistral 7B** (main + mm-proj)
- **LLaVA 1.5 7B** (smaller, accessible)
- **Gemma 3 4B** (already in catalog — add `IsVisionModel: true` + its mm-proj URL)

Each entry gets `"IsVisionModel": true` and `"MmProjDownloadUrl": "https://..."`.

---

### 3. Services

#### [MODIFY] [IModelManagerService.cs](file:///c:/Users/User/source/repos/avikeid2007/Kairos.local/KaiROS.AI/Services/IModelManagerService.cs)
- Add `bool IsVisionModel` property.
- Add `string? MmProjLocalPath` property.

#### [MODIFY] [ModelManagerService.cs](file:///c:/Users/User/source/repos/avikeid2007/Kairos.local/KaiROS.AI/Services/ModelManagerService.cs)
- In [DownloadModelAsync](file:///c:/Users/User/source/repos/avikeid2007/Kairos.local/KaiROS.AI/Services/ModelManagerService.cs#139-196): if `IsVisionModel` is true, also download the mm-proj GGUF alongside the main model.
- In [SetActiveModelAsync](file:///c:/Users/User/source/repos/avikeid2007/Kairos.local/KaiROS.AI/Services/ModelManagerService.cs#239-371): also load `LLavaWeights` from mm-proj path if present, and expose it.
- Add `GetLoadedLlavaWeights()` method.

#### [MODIFY] [IChatService.cs](file:///c:/Users/User/source/repos/avikeid2007/Kairos.local/KaiROS.AI/Services/IChatService.cs)
- Add `bool IsVisionReady` property (true when LLavaWeights loaded).
- Add overloads of [GenerateResponseStreamAsync](file:///c:/Users/User/source/repos/avikeid2007/Kairos.local/KaiROS.AI/Services/ChatService.cs#137-139) that accept `string? imagePath`.

#### [MODIFY] [ChatService.cs](file:///c:/Users/User/source/repos/avikeid2007/Kairos.local/KaiROS.AI/Services/ChatService.cs)
- On [InitializeContext](file:///c:/Users/User/source/repos/avikeid2007/Kairos.local/KaiROS.AI/Services/ChatService.cs#54-74): if `_modelManager.GetLoadedLlavaWeights()` is non-null, create `InteractiveExecutor(context, llavaWeights)` (multi-modal overload).
- In [GenerateResponseStreamAsync](file:///c:/Users/User/source/repos/avikeid2007/Kairos.local/KaiROS.AI/Services/ChatService.cs#137-139): if an imagePath is provided, embed the image reference `{imagePath}` into the user message text before passing to `_executor.InferAsync`. LLamaSharp parses `{path}` tokens, calls `LLavaWeights.CreateImageEmbeddings`, and processes them.
- Expose `IsVisionReady` from model manager state.

